# W4-b (card 427925ef) negative: `del` on an indexed list element — `del xs[0]` —
# is not supported. Codegen would lower it to `drop(<clone of xs[0]>)`, dropping a
# value-semantics COPY and leaving the stored list UNCHANGED (a silent no-op that
# byte-diverges from CPython, which removes the element). It is an honest typeck
# error instead, naming the working idiom `xs.pop(i)`. Rejected by `pyrst check`.
def main() -> None:
    xs: list[int] = [1, 2, 3]
    del xs[0]
    print(xs)
